The earthquake in Iran, which killed an estimated 50,000 people, was the world's fourth  largest earthquake in the last 50 years.
The Iranian earthquake registered 7.3 to 7.7 on the  Richter Scale.
The deadliest earthquake occurred in China in 1976, killing 200,000  people.
Unofficial estimates but the total at 800,000.
The second deadliest was a quake in  Soviet Turkmenia in 1948 which claimed 110,000 lives.
The third largest occurred in  Peru in 1970 and left 66,794 dead.
Earthquakes in Soviet Armenia, Guatemala, Morocco,  three others in Iran, round out the top ten list.
These earthquakes claimed between 12,000  and 25,000 lives. 
